A N A C T
RELATING TO MOTOR AND OTHER VEHICLES -- PASSING, USE OF LANES, AND
RULES OF THE ROAD
Introduced By: Senators LaMountain, Tikoian, and McKenney
Date Introduced: February 26, 2025
Referred To: Senate Judiciary
(Judiciary)
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 31-15-9 of the General Laws in Chapter 31-15 entitled "Passing, Use
2 of Lanes, and Rules of the Road" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 31-15-9. One way highways.
4 (a) The state traffic commission may designate any highway or any separate roadway under
5 its jurisdiction for one-way traffic and shall erect appropriate signs giving notice of one-way traffic.
6 (b) Upon a roadway designated and signposted for one-way traffic a vehicle shall be driven
7 only in the direction designated. Violations of this section are subject to fines enumerated in ยง 31-
8 41.1-4.
9 (c) Violations of this section are subject to fines enumerated in ยง 31-41.1-4 If a motorist
10 violates this section on an interstate highway or on an entrance or exit ramp connected to an
11 interstate highway, the motorist may be subject to a fine of up to five hundred dollars ($500) or
12 license suspension of up to six (6) months, or both.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
